ort dark hair, a beard, and intense blue eyes, with floating ice particles around him and cool blue light rising from below. He then appears in motion, wearing a red helmet and white outfit while airborne with skis or ski-like equipment, his body twisting in a controlled jump against the dark, snowy studio background. More close-ups return to a red boot on a ski edge or rail-like glowing line. Thin white guide boxes surround the boot, buckles, and contact points, highlighting the exact placement where the equipment meets the surface. A side view of the helmeted athlete shows a red helmet, reflective goggles, and a concentrated expression, with the blue-lit particles continuing behind him.\n\nErin Jackson reappears in the blue studio, now skating directly forward in slow, powerful form. Her white suit stands out against the dark background, and small snow or ice particles drift around her. She holds one arm close to her chest while the other arm and leg extend behind her, maintaining a low racing position. The scene then returns to broadcast-style competition footage: a speed skater in a black suit and orange visor races down the ice toward the viewer. White boards behind the rink display the red “TOYOTA” name and Toyota logo, and a small “LIVE” broadcast graphic with NBC and Olympic rings appears in the upper right. The skater drives forward with deep, rhythmic pushes, blade edges glinting on the ice.\n\nA celebratory moment follows. Erin, still in a black racing suit with white sleeves, lifts a large United States flag high over her head. The flag stretches above her, red and white stripes rippling and a blue field of white stars visible. She moves along the rink boards, smiling in profile. Behind her, “Beijing 2022” and Olympic rings are visible on the blue rink barrier, placing the moment at the Olympic venue.\n\nThe final snowy sequence shifts to a vast mountain face under bright daylight. A lone skier in a red jacket descends a steep, untouched white slope betw